Emails sent to government representatives by WTT site.

Emails are rendered by loader.render_to_string, where loader is django.template.loader, so you can use the same syntax here as rendering normal html.

Allowed variables are:

current_site.domain  
  Current site domain. This value is actually stored in django_site table


mail
   an Email model object. This contains everything from sender to recipient name.
  
mail.sender_name
   senders full name 
   
mail.public
   a booleasn whether a mail is public or private

messageBody
   Whole text of message